  <data name="Help_Intro.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Here you will find step-by-step guides for setting up optional features.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Help_GeoTitle.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Set up the GeoLite2 database (geolocation)</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Help_GeoIntro.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>To display country and location information for IP addresses, the free MaxMind GeoLite2 City database is required. For licensing reasons it is not bundled and must be installed manually once.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Help_GeoStep1.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>1. Create a free MaxMind account at maxmind.com (GeoLite2 sign-up).</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Help_GeoStep2.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>2. In your MaxMind account, download the “GeoLite2 City” database in MaxMind DB (.mmdb) format and extract the archive.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Help_GeoStep3.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>3. Copy the file “GeoLite2-City.mmdb” into the folder %AppData%\NetOverseer\geoip\ (the button below opens this folder).</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Help_GeoStep4.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>4. Restart NetOverseer. Optionally, you can enter a MaxMind license key on the “Reputation” tab so the database updates automatically.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Help_GeoMaxMindLink.Content" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Open MaxMind GeoLite2</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Help_OpenGeoFolder.Content" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Open GeoIP folder</value>
  </data>

